25/*
26 * This file defines the private interface between the
27 * AMD kernel graphics drivers and the AMD KFD.
28 */
29
30#ifndef KGD_KFD_INTERFACE_H_INCLUDED
31#define KGD_KFD_INTERFACE_H_INCLUDED
32
33#include <linux/types.h>
34
35struct pci_dev;
36
37#define KFD_INTERFACE_VERSION 1
38
39struct kfd_dev;
40struct kgd_dev;
41
42struct kgd_mem;
43
44enum kgd_memory_pool {
45 KGD_POOL_SYSTEM_CACHEABLE = 1,
46 KGD_POOL_SYSTEM_WRITECOMBINE = 2,
47 KGD_POOL_FRAMEBUFFER = 3,
48};
49
50enum kgd_engine_type {
51 KGD_ENGINE_PFP = 1,
52 KGD_ENGINE_ME,
53 KGD_ENGINE_CE,
54 KGD_ENGINE_MEC1,
55 KGD_ENGINE_MEC2,
56 KGD_ENGINE_RLC,
57 KGD_ENGINE_SDMA1,
58 KGD_ENGINE_SDMA2,
59 KGD_ENGINE_MAX
60};
61
62struct kgd2kfd_shared_resources {
63 /* Bit n == 1 means VMID n is available for KFD. */
64 unsigned int compute_vmid_bitmap;
65
66 /* Compute pipes are counted starting from MEC0/pipe0 as 0. */
67 unsigned int first_compute_pipe;
68
69 /* Number of MEC pipes available for KFD. */
70 unsigned int compute_pipe_count;
71
72 /* Base address of doorbell aperture. */
73 phys_addr_t doorbell_physical_address;
74
75 /* Size in bytes of doorbell aperture. */
76 size_t doorbell_aperture_size;
77
78 /* Number of bytes at start of aperture reserved for KGD. */
79 size_t doorbell_start_offset;
80};
81
82/**
83 * struct kfd2kgd_calls
84 *
85 * @init_gtt_mem_allocation: Allocate a buffer on the gart aperture.
86 * The buffer can be used for mqds, hpds, kernel queue, fence and runlists
87 *
88 * @free_gtt_mem: Frees a buffer that was allocated on the gart aperture
89 *
90 * @get_vmem_size: Retrieves (physical) size of VRAM
91 *
92 * @get_gpu_clock_counter: Retrieves GPU clock counter
93 *
94 * @get_max_engine_clock_in_mhz: Retrieves maximum GPU clock in MHz
95 *
96 * @program_sh_mem_settings: A function that should initiate the memory
97 * properties such as main aperture memory type (cache / non cached) and
98 * secondary aperture base address, size and memory type.
99 * This function is used only for no cp scheduling mode.
100 *
101 * @set_pasid_vmid_mapping: Exposes pasid/vmid pair to the H/W for no cp
102 * scheduling mode. Only used for no cp scheduling mode.
103 *
104 * @init_pipeline: Initialized the compute pipelines.
105 *
106 * @hqd_load: Loads the mqd structure to a H/W hqd slot. used only for no cp
107 * sceduling mode.
108 *
109 * @hqd_sdma_load: Loads the SDMA mqd structure to a H/W SDMA hqd slot.
110 * used only for no HWS mode.
111 *
112 * @hqd_is_occupies: Checks if a hqd slot is occupied.
113 *
114 * @hqd_destroy: Destructs and preempts the queue assigned to that hqd slot.
115 *
116 * @hqd_sdma_is_occupied: Checks if an SDMA hqd slot is occupied.
117 *
118 * @hqd_sdma_destroy: Destructs and preempts the SDMA queue assigned to that
119 * SDMA hqd slot.
120 *
121 * @get_fw_version: Returns FW versions from the header
122 *
123 * This structure contains function pointers to services that the kgd driver
124 * provides to amdkfd driver.
125 *
126 */
127struct kfd2kgd_calls {
128 int (*init_gtt_mem_allocation)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, size_t size,
129 void **mem_obj, uint64_t *gpu_addr,
130 void **cpu_ptr);
131
132 void (*free_gtt_mem)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, void *mem_obj);
133
134 uint64_t (*get_vmem_size)(struct kgd_dev *kgd);
135 uint64_t (*get_gpu_clock_counter)(struct kgd_dev *kgd);
136
137 uint32_t (*get_max_engine_clock_in_mhz)(struct kgd_dev *kgd);
138
139 /* Register access functions */
140 void (*program_sh_mem_settings)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, uint32_t vmid,
141 uint32_t sh_mem_config, uint32_t sh_mem_ape1_base,
142 uint32_t sh_mem_ape1_limit, uint32_t sh_mem_bases);
143
144 int (*set_pasid_vmid_mapping)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, unsigned int pasid,
145 unsigned int vmid);
146
147 int (*init_pipeline)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, uint32_t pipe_id,
148 uint32_t hpd_size, uint64_t hpd_gpu_addr);
149
150 int (*init_interrupts)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, uint32_t pipe_id);
151
152 int (*hqd_load)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, void *mqd, uint32_t pipe_id,
153 uint32_t queue_id, uint32_t __user *wptr);
154
155 int (*hqd_sdma_load)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, void *mqd);
156
157 bool (*hqd_is_occupied)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, uint64_t queue_address,
158 uint32_t pipe_id, uint32_t queue_id);
159
160 int (*hqd_destroy)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, uint32_t reset_type,
161 unsigned int timeout, uint32_t pipe_id,
162 uint32_t queue_id);
163
164 bool (*hqd_sdma_is_occupied)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, void *mqd);
165
166 int (*hqd_sdma_destroy)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, void *mqd,
167 unsigned int timeout);
168
169 int (*address_watch_disable)(struct kgd_dev *kgd);
170 int (*address_watch_execute)(struct kgd_dev *kgd,
171 unsigned int watch_point_id,
172 uint32_t cntl_val,
173 uint32_t addr_hi,
174 uint32_t addr_lo);
175 int (*wave_control_execute)(struct kgd_dev *kgd,
176 uint32_t gfx_index_val,
177 uint32_t sq_cmd);
178 uint32_t (*address_watch_get_offset)(struct kgd_dev *kgd,
179 unsigned int watch_point_id,
180 unsigned int reg_offset);
181 bool (*get_atc_vmid_pasid_mapping_valid)(
182 struct kgd_dev *kgd,
183 uint8_t vmid);
184 uint16_t (*get_atc_vmid_pasid_mapping_pasid)(
185 struct kgd_dev *kgd,
186 uint8_t vmid);
187 void (*write_vmid_invalidate_request)(struct kgd_dev *kgd,
188 uint8_t vmid);
189
190 uint16_t (*get_fw_version)(struct kgd_dev *kgd,
191 enum kgd_engine_type type);
192};
193
194/**
195 * struct kgd2kfd_calls
196 *
197 * @exit: Notifies amdkfd that kgd module is unloaded
198 *
199 * @probe: Notifies amdkfd about a probe done on a device in the kgd driver.
200 *
201 * @device_init: Initialize the newly probed device (if it is a device that
202 * amdkfd supports)
203 *
204 * @device_exit: Notifies amdkfd about a removal of a kgd device
205 *
206 * @suspend: Notifies amdkfd about a suspend action done to a kgd device
207 *
208 * @resume: Notifies amdkfd about a resume action done to a kgd device
209 *
210 * This structure contains function callback pointers so the kgd driver
211 * will notify to the amdkfd about certain status changes.
212 *
213 */
214struct kgd2kfd_calls {
215 void (*exit)(void);
216 struct kfd_dev* (*probe)(struct kgd_dev *kgd, struct pci_dev *pdev,
217 const struct kfd2kgd_calls *f2g);
218 bool (*device_init)(struct kfd_dev *kfd,
219 const struct kgd2kfd_shared_resources *gpu_resources);
220 void (*device_exit)(struct kfd_dev *kfd);
221 void (*interrupt)(struct kfd_dev *kfd, const void *ih_ring_entry);
222 void (*suspend)(struct kfd_dev *kfd);
223 int (*resume)(struct kfd_dev *kfd);
224};
225
226bool kgd2kfd_init(unsigned interface_version,
227 const struct kgd2kfd_calls **g2f);
228
229#endif /* KGD_KFD_INTERFACE_H_INCLUDED */
